From d1e47c264499712b817baf80433b1f2288176ded Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESTI Contributors <esti@example.local>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:27:10 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] Dashboard: condensed mosaic, Action Center split into
 tiles, square tags

- Dashboard grid switched to Carbon condensed (1px gutters) with a matching
  1px row-gap so tiles read as a flush mosaic; zone headers get breathing
  room via the structural .esti-zone-head helper
- Action Center split from one large tile into four equal lg=4 tiles, each
  with its own health edge: Overdue collections (alert/ok), Approvals pending
  (watch/ok), Ready to bill (ok/neutral, with count + estimated value), and
  Risk & capacity (high-risk projects + overloaded members)
- Tags render with square corners app-wide via a geometry-only colourless
  border-radius: 0 override in styles.scss
- CARBON-UI-DIRECTION.md documents the health-edge tokens, outline-tag rule,
  square tag geometry, and condensed dashboard grid

Co-Authored-By: Codex Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
